Web Page Design with CSS

CSS allows you to create rules that control

the way that each individual box (and the contents

of that box) is presented.

Example Styles

Boxes

Width and Height

Borders (color, width, and style)

Background color and images

Position in the browser window

Text

Typeface

Size

Color

Italics, bold, uppercase, lowercase, small-caps

Specific

There are specific ways in which you can style certain

elements such as lists, tables, and forms
